"Jiangxi will train 10,000 rural elementary school music and physical education teachers within three years - Xinhua News."
"Xinhua News, Nanchang, May 22nd: The reporter recently learned from the Jiangxi Provincial Education Department that in order to enhance the ability to guarantee the teacher team for the shortage of disciplines and to achieve equal development of rural compulsory education, since 2016, Jiangxi Province has planned to use three years to train each of the 10,000 qualified music, art, and physical education teachers for all rural (township and below) elementary schools in the province."
"It is understood that the training targets are teachers under the age of 45 with a music, art, or physical education background or talent who are able to teach other subjects as well, in rural elementary schools throughout Jiangxi province."
"Through the training, they will be equipped with the basic knowledge and teaching skills in the music, physical education, and art subjects, update their teaching ideas and concepts, master modern teaching methods, improve their ability in teaching the subjects, activity design, campus culture, and self-development. The goal is to build a team of multi-skilled music, physical education, and art teachers, and alleviate the shortage of such teachers in rural areas."
"To ensure the quality and effectiveness of the training, Jiangxi also plans to train one music, art, and physical education teacher in each of the 100 counties (cities, districts) in the province, a total of 300 training participants, to comprehensively improve their ability in teaching demonstration and leadership, activity design and organization, training, and building online research workshops. They will play the role of teaching, demonstrating, guiding, and supervising."